.TH "i40e_tx_map" 9 "i40e_tx_map" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i40e_tx_map \- Build the Tx descriptor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" i40e_tx_map
.BI "(struct i40e_ring *tx_ring "  ","
.BI "struct sk_buff *skb "  ","
.BI "struct i40e_tx_buffer *first "  ","
.BI "u32 tx_flags "  ","
.BI "const u8 hdr_len "  ","
.BI "u32 td_cmd "  ","
.BI "u32 td_offset "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tx_ring" 12
ring to send buffer on
.IP "skb" 12
send buffer
.IP "first" 12
first buffer info buffer to use
.IP "tx_flags" 12
collected send information
.IP "hdr_len" 12
size of the packet header
.IP "td_cmd" 12
the command field in the descriptor
.IP "td_offset" 12
offset for checksum or crc
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 on success, -1 on failure to DMA
